               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nIn this text, we will examine a distinct methodology for multiplication that was possibly used by the Maya (<htcite0>; <htcite1>). However, as with addition, it is not possible to state with certainty how these calculations were performed, due to the absence of textual records explicitly describing their methods.\n\nSince their methods differed from ours, this leads us to the following reflection:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "9e7d0cea-d968-4bd5-886e-bc08c824e7ca",
                     "text": "Díaz, Ruy D.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2006",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ced67eaf-7378-4589-9166-07f799969e3e",
                     "text": "Catepillán, Ximena",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: On methodology</b><br /><br />Does a different way of performing multiplication yield different results?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_common",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### A Common Conclusion\n\nWhen describing the multiplication performed by the Maya, Dr. Ximena Catepillán suggests that, for small numbers, the Indigenous peoples possibly repeated a number a certain number of times (<htcite0>). This conclusion is analogous to that of Dhavit Prem in the *\"Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay\"* method (<htcite1>; <htcite2>), which we previously studied (<htcite3>). We revisit this idea here as a reminder, through Table 1, in which you can choose two values between 0 and 9 and perform the multiplication operation:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ced67eaf-7378-4589-9166-07f799969e3e",
                     "text": "Catepillán, Ximena",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "pp. 354 - 363",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "2d2ea4a5-506b-4dbf-aaa4-3a10a8fbbd9c",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "",
                        "year": "",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "c4c2c00d-7878-42da-9cc4-060cd7f8d225",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Yupana (Multiplicação)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p style=\"margin: auto; with: 50%;\"><input type=\"number\" value=\"7\" min=\"0\" max=\"9\" id=\"ia2yupana0\" /> × <input type=\"number\" value=\"8\" min=\"0\" max=\"9\" id=\"ia2yupana1\" />:  <input type=\"radio\" value=\"values\" name=\"yupanaradio\" /> <b>Values</b> <input type=\"radio\" value=\"calcular\" name=\"yupanaradio\" /> <b>Calculations</b></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana0\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\"><i>Yupana</i></th><th>Values</th><th>Results</th><th>Movements</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f1\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f1\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f1\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f1\"><span id=\"vl1\"></span> x <span id=\"vr1\"></span></td><td id=\"tc6f1\">&nbsp;</td><td id=\"tc7f1\" rowspan=\"5\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf2\"><td id=\"tc1f2\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f2\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f2\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f2\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f2\"><span id=\"vl2\"></span> x <span id=\"vr2\"></span></td><td id=\"tc6f2\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf3\"><td id=\"tc1f3\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f3\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f3\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f3\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f3\"><span id=\"vl3\"></span> x <span id=\"vr3\"></span></td><td id=\"tc6f3\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf4\"><td id=\"tc1f4\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f4\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f4\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f4\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f4\"><span id=\"vl4\"></span> x <span id=\"vr4\"></span></td><td id=\"tc6f4\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf5\"><td id=\"tc1f5\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f5\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f5\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f5\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f5\"><span id=\"vl5\"></span> x <span id=\"vr5\"></span></td><td id=\"tc6f5\">&nbsp;</td></tr></table>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "The Yupana consists of a table with four columns and five rows: The first column contains five circles; The second column has three circles; The third column has two circles; The last column contains only one circle; This pattern repeats across all rows. Adjacent to the Yupana, we have added two columns showing conventional numerical representations. Finally, we included a column describing all the summation steps performed to obtain the final result.",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\">Table 1: Representation of the Yupana according to Poma de Ayala (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8'); return false;\">Prem, Dhavit, pp. 355, <htdate0></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('f5b74f18-0bc4-46d2-8a5c-64dd80b74dd1'); return false;\">Poma de Ayala, Felipe Guaman, pp. 361 - 362, <htdate1></a>).</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2018",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "1615",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_maya_step",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Multiplying with Grids\n\nAlthough we cannot state with certainty that the Mesoamericans used grids to perform multiplications, we also cannot dismiss the evidence indicating the possibility that this method may have been used (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).\n\nIn this section, we follow the works of Ruy D. Díaz and Ximena Catepillán, showing step by step how to carry out the same operations. We will begin working with numbers of only two orders (*K’iin*, *Winal*), performing the multiplication **21 × 42 = 882**.\n\n#### Understanding the Grid\n\nFirst, we set up a grid in the following format (<htcite2>):",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "9e7d0cea-d968-4bd5-886e-bc08c824e7ca",
                     "text": "Díaz, Ruy D.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2006",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ced67eaf-7378-4589-9166-07f799969e3e",
                     "text": "Catepillán, Ximena",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ced67eaf-7378-4589-9166-07f799969e3e",
                     "text": "Catepillán, Ximena",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"emptyGrid\" class=\"tableTen\"> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\">&nbsp;</td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Second order</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>First order</b></td></tr>  <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Second order</b></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>First order</b></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr> </table></p> <p class=\"desc\">Table 2 – multiplication grid.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "It is important to note that the numerical orders are arranged so that those of greater value are closer together, while those of lesser value are placed farther apart. To make this clearer, we write the multiplication we are performing (**21 × 42**) in decimal format:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"decGrid\" class=\"tableTen\"> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\">&nbsp;</td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>4</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>2</b></td></tr>  <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>2</b></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>1</b></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr> </table></p> <p class=\"desc\">Calculation 1: Multiplication of 21 by 42.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### Writing in the Grid\n\nSince this is a Mesoamerican method, we will convert the decimal numbers to Mesoamerican notation before proceeding:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"decGrid\" class=\"tableTen\"> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\">&nbsp;</td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgt00\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgt00', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_4.png\" /></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgt10\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgt10', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td></tr>  <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b><img id=\"imgl00\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgl00', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgl10\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgl10', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_1.png\" /></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr> </table></p> <p class=\"desc\">Calculation 2: Multiplication of 21 by 42.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### Multiplying\n\nBefore observing how the Maya may have carried out the operation, let us recall how we perform multiplication in our own system (<htcite0>):",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "4ee22ab8-e17c-48a8-8289-c8538aba77bf",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Rereading",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p style=\"text-align=center\"><center>Multiplication by: <input class=\"ordercheck\" type=\"checkbox\" id=\"1\" /> Units <input class=\"ordercheck\" type=\"checkbox\" id=\"2\" /> Tens</center></p><p style=\"text-align=center\"><center>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmtc2\">2 </span><span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmtc1\">1 </span> <br />× &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmbc2\">4 </span><span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmbc1\">2 </span><br />_________<br /></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmptrc2\">4 </span><span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmptrc1\">2 </span><br />+ <span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmpbrc3\">8 </span><span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmpbrc2\">4 </span><span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmpbrc1\">0 </span><br />_________<br />&nbsp; <span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmrc3\">8 </span><span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmrc2\">8 </span><span class=\"multexample1\" id=\"mmrc1\">2 </span></center></p><p class=\"desc\">Calculation 3: Multiplication of 21 by 42.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "In Calculation 3, we first multiply 21 by the unit (2) and then by the ten (40) — which some simplify as *\"multiplying by 4.\"* In the grids, the process is similar: we multiply the numbers in pairs and place the result in the corresponding square. Use the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrow-right\" style=\"color:#0f0;\"></i> to do math and the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate\" style=\"color:#00f;\"></i> to restart:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"decGrid\" class=\"tableTen\"> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\">&nbsp;</td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgt0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgt0', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgt1\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgt1', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td><b>Controles</b></td></tr>  <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b><img id=\"imgl0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgl0', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_1.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgm3\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm3', '0%')\" src=\"\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgm1\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm1', '0%')\" src=\"\" /></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrow-right upArrowWithFA\" id=\"traineeUp3\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate downArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size:4em;color:#00f;\" id=\"traineeDown3\"></i></td></tr> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgl1\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgl1', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_1.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgm2\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm2', '0%')\" src=\"\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgm0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm0', '0%')\" src=\"\" /></td></tr> </table></p> <p class=\"desc\">Calculation 4: Multiplication of 21 by 42.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "In the Maya grids, at this stage it is not necessary to multiply in the same order as in the decimal method. However, we chose to keep the order to make it easier to identify the multiplied numbers.\n\n#### Repositioning\n\nAt this stage, we read the values along the diagonals, adding them. To simplify understanding, we repeat Calculation 4 with the diagonals highlighted in different colors in Calculation 5:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"decGrid\" class=\"tableTen\"> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\">&nbsp;</td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgt000\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgt000', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgt100\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgt100', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td></tr>  <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b><img id=\"imgl000\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgl000', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_1.png\" /></td><td style=\"background-color: lightyellow\"><img id=\"imgm300\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm300', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td style=\"background-color: lightgreen\"><img id=\"imgm100\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm100', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><img id=\"imgl100\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgl100', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_1.png\" /></td><td style=\"background-color: lightgreen\"><img id=\"imgm200\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm200', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td style=\"background-color: lightgray\"><img id=\"imgm000\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgm000', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td></tr> </table></p> <p class=\"desc\">Calculation 5: Multiplication of 21 by 42.</p>",
